# 5. いざ、準備開始！

Tsukasa: Alright, I believe we all have a copy of the script.
Mizuki: Wow, it's bound and everything...!
Airi: It really feels like we're getting ready to do a show now.
Tsukasa: I'm sorry for asking you both to also appear in the show. I know you're very busy fixing the costumes...
Mizuki: Not a problem! I'm actually really happy about getting to do a show with you again, Tsukasa. I mean, the one we did at the chocolate factory was so much fun!
Nene: While we're on the subject, Momoi, are you going to be okay? You also have your group to think about...
Airi: Oh, that won't be an issue. The others gave me the green light after I told them about Mr. Inuyama.
Airi: They told me to go out there and do my best since they understand what I want to do.
Nene: I see... I'm glad to hear that.
Tsukasa: Anyway, let's start going over the story!
Mizuki: It's based on the synopsis Mr. Inuyama gave us the other day, right? A feline hero protects a carnival...?
Tsukasa: Yes. It takes place at a carnival which has a large Ferris wheel as its main attraction...
Tsukasa: The story revolves around our hero, Nyantaro, taking part in an epic battle against a pair of mischievous cat sisters.
Airi: An epic battle? I don't remember it being quite so dramatic...
Tsukasa: The sisters showed up at the carnival one day and began pulling pranks on all the guests.
Tsukasa: Nyantaro brought them to justice each time, but that did nothing to deter them from coming back time and again...
Tsukasa: Then, one day, the sisters come up with the most dastardly plan imaginable...!
Nene: They stop the Ferris wheel, right?
Tsukasa: Yes, and it saddens many of the guests since it's the carnival's main attraction.
Tsukasa: When the sisters run off with the control switch, Nyantaro gives chase in order to get the carnival guests smiling once more...
Tsukasa: The sisters are quick, and they don't make it easy, but Nyantaro does manage to catch them and reactivate the Ferris wheel.
Tsukasa: The sisters finally see the error of their ways, and the guests return to smiling. The end!
Mizuki: Man, the climax sounds really exciting!
Mizuki: And I can't wait to see how Nyantaro chases after those sisters!
Tsukasa: Ah, by the way, Mr. Inuyama played the lead during his carnival's opening celebration.
Mizuki: Wait, really?!
Nene: Hang on a second... Do you think the Nyantaro in this show is based off the real Nyantaro?
Tsukasa: No, they apparently put on this show around twenty years ago...
Tsukasa: Which means Nyantaro was named after the hero from this story.
Airi: I see... In other words, he's the embodiment of some really precious memories.
Mizuki: Mr. Inuyama must've loved this show a lot...
Tsukasa: *Nod* And that's a powerful source of motivation!
Mizuki: Definitely! We've gotta make this the best show ever!
Airi: Yeah, let's do our best! What do you need us to do next, Tenma?
Tsukasa: Ah, we need to decide roles now.
Tsukasa: Starting with Nyantaro.
Tsukasa: Alright, we all have our roles now.
Tsukasa: The protagonist, Nyantaro, will be played by... Me, Tsukasa Tenma!
Mizuki: As for the cat sisters, Airi will play the older one and Kusanagi will play the younger one.
Airi: I'm really looking forward to working with you, Kusanagi! I can't wait for you to teach me more about acting like you did during Shibu Schools Fest!
Nene: Y-Yes, I'm also looking forward to working with you...!
Tsukasa: And you'll be playing one of the carnival's guests, Akiyama. Although, it is a tad unfortunate that you're going to be all by yourself...
Mizuki: Hmm... Yeah...
Mizuki: My plan's to pull out all the stops and really act out having a fun day, but I feel like I can only do so much on my own...
Mizuki: If only we had at least one more person. Isn't there anyone we can ask...?
Tsukasa: Good question. Unfortunately, Rui and Emu are busy that day, and I'm not sure who else could help us...
Airi: Actually, I think I know just the person to ask...
Nene: Huh?
Airi: When I told the others in my group about this, Minori's eyes lit up and she said, “Doing a show with them sounds like so much fun!”
Airi: She even said that she wants to help out in any way she can, so we could have her join the cast.
Tsukasa: Oh, Hanasato, you say?! She's sort of my dance student... It'd be great to have her on board!
Mizuki: I'd also love to work with Minori! If anything, I should be the one asking her to join us since she's my favorite idol...!
Airi: Hehe. Then, I'll try asking her.
Mizuki: Hehehe. This is gonna be so much fun♪
Nene: That should take care of our casting problem. What else do we need to check up on...?
Airi: Come to think of it, how are the costumes coming along? I've been fixing the accessories and stuff bit by bit...
Mizuki: I'm working on the hero's costume right now. It was pretty beat up, but I should be able to get it back in shape!
Mizuki: As for the sisters, their cat ears and a couple other accessories were all that was left. We sorta have to use clothes you and Kusanagi already have for the outfits.
Mizuki: To compensate, I'm gonna make everything look really cute by attaching a bunch of ribbons and stuff! So, stay tuned!
Airi: Hehe. I can't wait to see what you make! Also, we should meet up to work on costume stuff together!
Tsukasa: Alright, I'm glad to hear that we all seem to know what to do.
Nene: Yeah. But we only have a week and change until the final day...
Tsukasa: I know. How about a toast to celebrate us entering the preparation phase of our show?
Nene: Wait, does that need a toast...?
Tsukasa: Of course! We need to keep ourselves motivated!
Airi: I already finished my drink... But still, it might be a good way to help us feel more like a team.
Mizuki: Yeah! Let's do it♪
Tsukasa: Then, raise your glasses, you three.
Tsukasa: This may be a short show, but we don't have much time to practice...
Tsukasa: As challenging as this endeavor is going to be, let's make sure our show puts smiles on the faces of Mr. Inuyama and all the guests! Cheers!
Airi, Mizuki & Nene: Cheers!
